"n.诡辩 【英】 n.诡辩 (subtly deceptive reasoning or argumentation ) 无 【记】philosopher哲学家，就是philo 爱 + sophe- 诡辩，爱诡辩的人；sophomore 大二学生就是sopho睿智，诡辩 + more 更加会诡辩的 sophistry (n.)  ""specious but fallacious reasoning,"" mid-14c., from Old French sophistrie (Modern French sophisterie), from Medieval Latin sophistria, from Latin sophista, sophistes (see sophist). ""Sophistry applies to reasoning as sophism to a single argument"" [Century Dictionary]."
